melot</i> (from Ameline), <i>Ellot</i> (from Ellen), and <i>Gillota</i> (from Gillian).","English: from Middle English <i>lot(t)e</i> ‘lot, portion’ (Old English <i>hlot</i>), in the sense of an allotted share of land, hence a status name for someone who held such a plot.","German: from a pet form of   Ludwig  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lotts","meanings":["English: patronymic or metronymic from   Lott   1.","Possibly an altered form of German   Lotz  ."]},{"name":"Ludwig","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Otto, Erwin, Ernst, Hans, Fritz, Klaus, Franz, Guenter, Horst, Claus, Erna.","German and Dutch (of German origin): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hlūd</i> ‘famous’ + <i>wīg</i> ‘war’. This was the name of the founder of the Frankish dynasty, recorded in Latin chronicles as <i>Chlodovechus</i> (see   Louis  ), and <i>Ludovicus</i>, which became German <i>Ludwig</i>. This became a hereditary name in the Wittelsbach family, the royal family of Bavaria."]}]},{"name":"Lady","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>lavedi</i>, <i>levedi</i>, <i>ladi</i> ‘lady, female head of a household, woman, wife’ (Old English <i>hlǣfdige</i>). As a man's name it may have been used in mockery, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘Morning dew’; also ‘generosity’."]}]},{"name":"Dorothy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Dorothea .  The name was not used in the Middle Ages, but was taken up in the 15th century and became common thereafter. It was borne by the American film star  Dorothy Lamour  (  1914–1996 , born  Dorothy Kaumeyer )."],"variants":[{"name":"Dorothee","meanings":["Usual English form of   Dorothea .  The name was not used in the Middle Ages, but was taken up in the 15th century and became common thereafter. It was borne by the American film star  Dorothy Lamour  (  1914–1996 , born  Dorothy Kaumeyer )."]},{"name":"Dorothie","meanings":["Usual English form of   Dorothea .  The name was not used in the Middle Ages, but was taken up in the 15th century and became common thereafter. It was borne by the American film star  Dorothy Lamour  (  1914–1996 , born  Dorothy Kaumeyer )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Dorothy Lott was born on 30 June 1546, in Canterbury, Kent, England, United Kingdom, her father, Lett Earl Lott, was 27 and her mother, Stella, was 27. She had at least 1 daughter with William Cowell Clarke. She died on 12 May 1611, in Bocking, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 64."},"et":{"30 Jun 1546–12 May 1611":"30. juuni 1546–12. mai 1611","1546–1611":"1546–1611","1540–1586":"1540–1586","1586–Female":"1586–Surnud","1520–Male":"1520–Surnud","1520–Female":"1520–Surnud","Aft. 1586":"pärast 1586","1546":"1546","1611":"1611","1520":"1520","1586":"1586","30 Jun 1546":"30. juuni 1546","16 JAN 1586":"16. jaanuar 1586","1540":"1540","12 May 1611":"12. mai 1611","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St George Martyr, Canterbury, New Zealand":"Canterbury, Canterbury, Uus-Meremaa","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"30 Jun 1546–12 May 1611":"30. kesäkuuta 1546–12. toukokuuta 1611","1546–1611":"1546–1611","1540–1586":"1540–1586","1586–Female":"1586–Kuollut","1520–Male":"1520–Kuollut","1520–Female":"1520–Kuollut","Aft. 1586":"1586 jälkeen","1546":"1546","1611":"1611","1520":"1520","1586":"1586","30 Jun 1546":"30. kesäkuuta 1546","16 JAN 1586":"16. tammikuuta 1586","1540":"1540","12 May 1611":"12. toukokuuta 1611","Bocking, Essex, England":"Bocking, Essex